messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
My daughter is choking on a bouncy ball.
Okay, and you're at 25-25 North 10th Street?
Yes.
Is she able to breathe?
No.
Okay, I'm going to get the ambulance on the way. Somebody will guide you through the Heimlich maneuver. Stay on the line, okay?
Yep.
How old is she?
Seven.
Okay, are you able to get behind her?
Is she okay? No.
It's okay. Is she really turning purple?
No, that's my three-year-old.
Okay, can you have someone stand behind her?
My son is behind her right now.
Okay, wrap his arms around her abdomen. Right around her abdomen. And then lift up and towards him.
Oh my God, she's about to pass out.
Okay, lift up and towards him. Up and towards her. Keep going.
Oh my God, she's turning red now!
Okay. My partner has the ambulance on the way.
Thank you.
Okay, tell me what's going on right now.
Are you okay? Keep going up and towards her right into her abdomen. A little bit higher than the abdomen. You're hurting her. I can't do it.
You keep trying. Oh my God, I cannot watch this. Keep going. The ambulance is on its way.
She's crying.
She is crying. That means she's getting some air. That's good.
She got it out. She puked it out.
Thank God. Excellent.
Oh my God.
They're going to still come over and check on her to make sure she's okay.
Thank you so much.
All right. They're on the way. I'm going to let you go then.
Thank you very much.
You're very welcome.
